span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\"><span style=\"color:black\">&middot;</span></span></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,\"><span style=\"color:black\">Context is king--</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,\"><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp;Google now uses latent semantic indexing (LSI), that understands how words relate. So, it is not helpful to stuff the content with your keyword phrases.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:48px; text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial\"><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\"><span style=\"color:black\">&middot;</span></span></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,\"><span style=\"color:black\">Read the searcher&rsquo;s intent--</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"background-color:#fcfcfc\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,\"><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp;So, consider your end users&rsquo; intent behind using certain keywords that you want to rank for.</span></span></span></span><strong>&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,\"><span style=\"color:black\">Definitions, Comparisons,&nbsp;Price/cost information, Top/best lists etc. type of content works well for Zero position.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-size:13.3333px\"><span style=\"backgrou